data.content:
## Sync I/O on Cosmos DB is fully removed in EF Core 11

In .NET 10, you could opt in to sync-over-async with the Cosmos provider. **In EF Core 11, that opt-in is gone** â€” all synchronous I/O APIs (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`, etc.) **always throw**. There is no workaround; you must go async.

### Fix: convert every method to its async equivalent

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key mapping:**
| .NET 10 (sync) | .NET 11 (required) |
|---|---|
| `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `First()` | `await FirstAsync()` |
| `Count()` | `await CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `await SaveChangesAsync()` |

This will ripple through your callers â€” every call site must also become `async`/`await` up the chain. Tracking issue: [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059).
